---
import FeedbackSection from '../components/FeedbackSection.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Test Feedback Component - Fluxzero Docs</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/src/styles/global.css">
</head>
<body style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;">
  <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 2rem auto; padding: 0 1rem;">
    <h1>Test Feedback Component</h1>

    <p>This page demonstrates the feedback display component with the current feedback API.</p>

    <h2>Sample Documentation Content</h2>
    <p>
      This is some sample documentation content about getting started with Fluxzero.
      Users would be able to select text here and leave feedback about it.
      The feedback would then be displayed in the component below.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Installation:</strong> To get started with Fluxzero, you need to install the SDK
      and configure your development environment. This involves setting up dependencies,
      configuring your project structure, and understanding the core concepts.
    </p>

    <!-- Feedback component for the getting started page -->
    <FeedbackSection slug="/docs/getting-started/introduction" />

    <h2>Additional Content</h2>
    <p>
      Here's some additional content that might also have feedback. The feedback component
      automatically fetches discussions that match the page slug pattern.
    </p>

    <p><em>Expected behavior:</em></p>
    <ul>
      <li>✅ Component should load and show loading spinner</li>
      <li>✅ API call should be made to <code>/api/feedback?slug=/docs/getting-started/introduction</code></li>
      <li>✅ Should display "No feedback yet" message (since no discussions exist with that slug)</li>
      <li>✅ Should show "Add your feedback" button</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</body>
</html>